{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-09-28-how-to-autoplay-audio-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To autoplay audio in react js, you can use  and then use it in  to autoplay on load. It will autoplay audio in react js‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To autoplay audio in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">audioRef</code> and then use it in <code class=\"language-text\">useEffect</code> to autoplay on load. It will autoplay audio in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to autoplay audio in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import react component.</h3>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useEffect<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> useRef <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Create a Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;audio ref={audioRef} controls></code> to autoplay audio in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>audio ref<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>audioRef<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> controls <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>source src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"music-1.mp3\"</span> type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"audio/mp3\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    Your browser does not support the audio element<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>audio<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Autoplay audio example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">react</code> and use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;audio ref={audioRef} controls ></code> to autoplay audio in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useEffect<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> useRef <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> audioRef <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useRef</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token function\">useEffect</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>audioRef<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>current<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      audioRef<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>current<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">play</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>aHoisting<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>audio ref<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>audioRef<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> controls <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>source src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"music-1.mp3\"</span> type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"audio/mp3\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        Your browser does not support the audio element<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>audio<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">ref={audioRef}</code> to autoplay audio in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 383px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c9f1a04b909c279b33bb8b12059ce371/8c481/autoplay-audio.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.84810126582278%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRloAAABXRUJQVlA4IE4AAADQAwCdASoUABAAPtFWo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJYwCdH8ADA18Eg6rBEwAA3mfO+Kp9XbozV7BgMz+WusAQBYxqE1vygokAUiixmx36OaDgAAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, autoplay, audio\"\n        title=\"React, autoplay, audio\"\n        src=\"/static/c9f1a04b909c279b33bb8b12059ce371/8c481/autoplay-audio.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c9f1a04b909c279b33bb8b12059ce371/81b7c/autoplay-audio.webp 158w,\n/static/c9f1a04b909c279b33bb8b12059ce371/6ea66/autoplay-audio.webp 315w,\n/static/c9f1a04b909c279b33bb8b12059ce371/8c481/autoplay-audio.webp 383w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to autoplay audio in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"September 28, 2024","description":"Example of autoplay audio in react js with step by step tutorial - aHoisting","social_image":{"absolutePath":"/Users/mac/Documents/hoisting/ahoisting/static/media/template/reactjs.jpg"}}},"prev":null,"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to autoplay a youtube video in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-09-27-how-to-autoplay-a-youtube-video-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2024-09-28-how-to-autoplay-audio-in-react-js/","prevSlug":null,"nextSlug":"/blog/2024-09-27-how-to-autoplay-a-youtube-video-in-react-js/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2555585279","2714594843","3159585216"]}